com.tomscz.afswinx.component.builders

Interface ComponentBuilder<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AFSwinxFormBuilder, AFSwinxTableBuilder, BaseComponentBuilder

    public interface ComponentBuilder<T>
    This interface specify operation which must provide every builder which is used to build AFSwinxTopLevelComponent. The generic class T should be the same as is class of builder
    Since:
    1.0.0.
    Author:
    Martin Tomasek (martin@toms-cz.com)

      • initBuilder

        T initBuilder(java.lang.String componentKeyName,
            AFSwinxConnection modelConnection,
            AFSwinxConnection dataConnection,
            AFSwinxConnection postConnection)
        This method init builder. It set existed connection to builder. There are connection types, which are used to retrieve model definitions, data and post data back.
        Parameters:
        componentKeyName - key in which you should retrieve this component back and do other staff with it
        modelConnection - connection to end point where model is defined couldn't be null
        dataConnection - connection to end point where data are, if null then component will be empty
        postConnection - connection to end point where will be send update or insert request if null no request is send
        Returns:
        it returns this builder which could be used to build

      • initBuilder

        T initBuilder(java.lang.String componentKeyName,
            java.io.InputStream connectionConfiguration,
            java.lang.String connectionKey,
            java.lang.String connectionValue)
        This method init builder. It set variable based on which will be obtained connections. There are connection types, which are used to retrieve model definitions, data and post data back.
        Parameters:
        componentKeyName - key in which you should retrieve this component back and do other staff with it
        connectionConfiguration - file in which will be found connection
        connectionKey - key of connection which will be found in connection configuration file
        connectionValue - value which will be added to connection configuration based on EL.
        Returns:
        it returns this builder which could be used to build
